#San Diego, CA

##Great Places to Eat
Kettner Exchange
Ironside Fish & Oyster has some of the best ambiance and seafood in San Diego
Juniper & Ivy is very popular as well - Contemporary American. Get a reservation here
Monello & Ben Cotto for Italian
C Level Lounge is a personal favorite, near the airport and has a fantastic view of the downtown skyline while also serving great food.

##Fun Things to Do
The San Diego Zoo is really great - even has pandas
Balboa park is beautiful and 100+ years old
Old town shows off some of California's Spanish Mission history

##Local Nightlife
The Gaslamp is the hottest area for late night bars and pubs, but it gets crowded
